---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTAButton from '../../../../components/CTAButton.astro';
import { COMPANY_INFO } from '../../../../utils/constants';

const lang = 'en';
const post = {
  title: 'Business Loan for Machinery Purchase Malaysia: The SME Guide',
  slug: 'business-loan-machinery-purchase-malaysia',
  excerpt: 'Need a business loan for machinery purchase in Malaysia? Learn how to get 100% financing, 0% down payment, and 24-hour approval even for used machines.',
  date: '2026-02-18',
  author: 'Ing Heng Credit Team',
  readTime: 12,
  category: 'Machinery Loan',
  image: '/images/blog/machinery-purchase-malaysia.jpg'
};

const keywords = ['business loan for machinery purchase malaysia', 'machinery loan malaysia', 'industrial equipment financing', 'sme machinery loan'],
  breadcrumbItems = [
  { label: 'Home', href: '/en' },
  { label: 'Blog', href: '/en/blog' },
  { label: post.title, href: `/en/blog/${post.slug}` }
];
---

<BaseLayout title={post.title} description={post.excerpt} lang={lang} keywords={keywords}>
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BlogPosting",
      "headline": "Business Loan for Machinery Purchase Malaysia: The SME Guide",
      "description": "Comprehensive guide for Malaysian SMEs on securing machinery loans with 0% down payment and no age limit on equipment.",
      "datePublished": "2026-02-18",
      "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Ing Heng Credit Team" },
      "publisher": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Ing Heng Credit & Leasing Sdn Bhd",
        "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": "https://inghengcredit.com/logo.png" }
      }
    }
  </script>

  <Breadcrumbs items={breadcrumbItems} />

  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <span class="text-sm font-semibold" style="color: #D4A574;">Machinery Loan</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mt-2" style="color: #2D1810; font-family: 'Bebas Neue', sans-serif; text-transform: uppercase;">{post.title}</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mt-4">{post.excerpt}</p>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">
        <span>{post.author}</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <time>{new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' })}</time>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>{post.readTime} min read</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>Buying new machinery is a massive milestone for any Malaysian SME. It means you're growing, taking on bigger contracts, and increasing your capacity. But let's be honest — the price tag can be terrifying. Whether it's a RM300,000 injection molding machine or a RM500,000 CNC station, paying cash upfront can cripple your cash flow.</p>

      <p>That's where a <strong>business loan for machinery purchase malaysia</strong> comes in. In this guide, we'll explain how you can get the tools you need without draining your bank account, even if the banks have said no before.</p>

      <h2>Why SMEs Need a Dedicated Machinery Loan</h2>
      <p>Most business owners try to use a generic business term loan for machinery. While possible, it's often not the best move. A dedicated machinery loan (or industrial hire purchase) is structured specifically for assets. Because the machine itself acts as collateral, you can often get better terms than an unsecured personal or business loan.</p>

      <p>At Ing Heng Credit, we've helped over 4,000 Malaysian businesses since 1985. We've seen firsthand how the right financing can turn a small workshop into a major factory.</p>

      <h2>The "Ing Heng" Advantage: 0% Down Payment</h2>
      <p>If you go to a traditional bank, they'll usually ask for a 20% to 30% down payment. For a RM200,000 machine, that's RM60,000 gone from your pocket immediately. That's money you could have used for raw materials or payroll.</p>

      <p><strong>We do things differently.</strong> For qualified SMEs, we offer 0% down payment and 100% financing. You get the machine, start producing, and pay as you earn. No huge upfront burden.</p>

      <h2>No Age Limit on Machinery</h2>
      <p>This is where most banks stop helping. Most commercial banks in Malaysia won't finance machinery that is older than 5 years. But in many industries, a 10-year-old machine works perfectly fine and costs half the price of a new one.</p>

      <p>Whether you're buying a brand-new unit from a dealer or a reliable 15-year-old machine from a friend, we can help. We have <strong>NO AGE LIMIT</strong> on the machinery we finance. If it helps your business grow, we'll find a way to finance it.</p>

      <h2>Common Machinery We Finance in Malaysia</h2>
      <p>We aren't just limited to "standard" gear. We understand various industries:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Manufacturing:</strong> CNC machines, lathes, milling, plastic injection, packaging lines.</li>
        <li><strong>Construction:</strong> Excavators, cranes, backhoes, bulldozers, pavers.</li>
        <li><strong>Logistics:</strong> Forklifts (diesel & electric), reach trucks, pallet stackers.</li>
        <li><strong>Food & Beverage:</strong> Industrial ovens, cold storage systems, bottling lines.</li>
        <li><strong>Printing:</strong> Large format printers, offset presses, binding machines.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Quick Comparison: Bank Loan vs. Ing Heng Credit</h2>
