      <p>We believe in transparent numbers. Most machinery loans in Malaysia use a flat interest rate. While rates vary based on the amount and tenure, here is a rough example:</p>
      <p><strong>Example Scenario:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Machine Price: RM100,000</li>
        <li>Down Payment: RM0 (100% Loan)</li>
        <li>Interest Rate: 4.5% p.a. (Flat)</li>
        <li>Tenure: 5 Years (60 Months)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>In this case, your monthly installment would be approximately <strong>RM2,042</strong>. If that machine helps you generate an extra RM10,000 in monthly revenue, the ROI is clear.</p>

      <h2>3 Mistakes to Avoid When Applying for a Machinery Loan</h2>
      <h3>1. Buying Without a Quote</h3>
      <p>Always get a formal quotation from the supplier first. This should include the machine's specifications, year of manufacture, and serial number. We need this to process your application.</p>

      <h3>2. Hiding CCRIS/CTOS Issues</h3>
      <p>We know life happens. If you have some past payment delays, be honest with us. We are more interested in your business's current cash flow and future potential than a minor hiccup from two years ago. When you're honest, we can structure a solution to help you.</p>

      <h3>3. Waiting Until the Last Minute</h3>
      <p>While we can approve in 24-48 hours, it's always better to get your financing pre-approved before you commit to the supplier. This gives you better bargaining power.</p>

